prompt_template:
Create a {ASPECT_RATIO} image in the "retro-future-chrome-portrait-dossier" visual style.

Subject: {SUBJECT}
Action: {SUBJECT_ACTION}
Prop/Product: {PRODUCT_OR_PROP}
Location: {LOCATION}
Background: {BACKGROUND_ELEMENTS}
Main text: {MAIN_TEXT}
Secondary text: {SECONDARY_TEXT}
Accent symbol: {ACCENT_SYMBOL}
Wardrobe/styling: {WARDROBE_STYLE}
Style fidelity anchors: {STYLE_FIDELITY_ANCHORS}
Source content to avoid: {SOURCE_CONTENT_TO_AVOID}

Apply these concrete style rules:
- Composition: build a dense asymmetric editorial poster with a technical dossier rail occupying roughly one third and a dominant extreme close-up portrait occupying roughly two thirds. Crop the subject through at least three frame edges. Reflow the modules intelligently for the selected aspect ratio while keeping the rail visibly narrower than the portrait field. Span thin cream modular grid lines across both zones.
- Dossier rail: stack one large wireframe diagram derived from the chosen prop, a bold forward-leaning display headline, small star or crosshair separators, compact original dossier labels, two optical or map-like modules, and a lower terrain, waveform, or contour mesh.
- Portrait: use flat posterized illustration with clean ink contours, simplified cream highlight planes, hot-magenta blush shadows, cobalt-violet contour shadows, and a strong oblique facial or helmet crop. Route newly shaped polished alloy ribbons, fragments, or reflective object parts diagonally through the portrait without covering essential anatomy.
- Typography: set the exact short main text once in a bold extended italic techno display face, cream on indigo, with tight tracking. Use the secondary text sparingly as compact condensed technical labels and abstract information texture. Do not add a creator credit or signature.
- Color: use approximately 45 percent midnight indigo, 25 percent warm cream and pale yellow, 20 percent hot magenta and cobalt, 8 percent coral, and 2 percent cyan or white glints. Avoid neutral photographic color.
- Texture and lighting: unify all surfaces with coarse controlled halftone dots, visible paper tooth, mild ink speckle, and slight color misregistration. Keep facial anatomy, silhouette, panel borders, and the main headline crisp. Use graphic high-contrast color planes instead of naturalistic lighting.
- Graphic elements: use hairline frames, irregular grid cells, registration crosses, wireframe meshes, optical waves, star sparks, specimen panels, and contour diagrams that relate to the selected case.

Avoid: photorealism, generic 3D render, clean flat vector minimalism, cinematic environment, soft lifestyle lighting, excessive blur, uncontrolled glitch, illegible headline, rainbow palette, white minimalist background, duplicated facial features, malformed hands, watermarks, usernames, QR codes, platform marks, logos, signatures, copied text, and exact source content.

Important content rule: match the extracted poster system first, then change the source content. Use the specified new subject, action, prop, environment, diagrams, headline, styling, chrome silhouette, and story premise while preserving the style fidelity anchors.
